/usr/bin/tex -ini -jobname tex lhplain.ini >/dev/null
/usr/bin/tex -ini -enc -jobname ru lhplain.ini >/dev/null

Until there is a way to account for offsets in dvitomp, use this for MetaPost labels
(and &%ru-no-offset instead of %&ru in verbatimtex):

sed /hoffset/,/catcode...=12/d lhplain.ini >mpost-no-offset.ini
/usr/bin/tex -ini mpost-no-offset.ini >/dev/null
/usr/bin/tex -ini -enc -jobname ru-no-offset mpost-no-offset.ini >/dev/null

-------------------

\xordcode is used to convert hyphenation tables from koi8-r to cp866 automatically

-------------------

To create font for MetaPost labels use this:

mftrace --formats=pfb --encoding=tex256.enc --magnification=2000 lhss10
